182
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:22,540
I'll go to the back and grab your clothes.

183
00:12:24,670 --> 00:12:26,150
Here.

184
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:29,270
I'm sorry, it's been two months.

185
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:31,080
No problem, I know you all are very busy.

186
00:12:31,080 --> 00:12:33,420
As long as you eventually remember to pick them up, it's fine.

187
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:35,390
Just don't be like the owner of this pile of clothes.

188
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:37,680
I finished washing these clothes and the owner has never showed up.

189
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:41,670
So you've just left them like this, until the owner picks them up then?

190
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:44,860
I trust that one day they'll return and pick them up.

191
00:12:44,860 --> 00:12:47,460
And there are many orders that have not been paid for yet.

192
00:12:48,620 --> 00:12:50,760
Why are there two bags?

193
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:53,300
Lawyer Zheng passed by just now, and I originally called out to him and asked him to take his clothes,

194
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,330
but he said that I could just hand over his clothes to you.

195
00:12:55,330 --> 00:12:57,040
Then he went downstairs.

196
00:12:57,040 --> 00:13:00,060
So he went to Lang Yuan to get a drink?

197
00:13:00,060 --> 00:13:01,870
I think so.

198
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:08,070
Do you often go downstairs to that bar to get a drink?

199
00:13:08,070 --> 00:13:11,010
He goes more often than I do, and he usually drags me there.

200
00:13:11,010 --> 00:13:15,080
Lawyer Fu, if you're really close with them,

201
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:19,770
could I bother you to ask them to quiet it down a bit?

202
00:13:19,770 --> 00:13:22,770
- Sure, that's no problem.
- Thank you.

203
00:13:29,260 --> 00:13:31,680
I thought you would just pick up our clothes and take them home.

204
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:35,150
- You should pick up your own clothes.
- You're so petty.

205
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:37,630
Nikita.

206
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:41,450
- Thank you.
- I haven't ordered for him yet.

207
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:44,150
Doesn't he have a gin and tonic every time?

208
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:50,040
Could I bother you to play a more quiet jazz music?

209
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:53,330
